						</tabular>
						<p>
							From the table we find there are 8 different ways to win the electoral college and candidates should definitely campaign in Large and Huge.
						</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<p>
							To find the fewest number of individual votes a candidate could win with; let's look at the table above. The combination of states with the fewest electoral votes is Huge and Small with 28 electoral votes. Let's see how many votes would be needed to win those two states.
						</p>
						<p>
							For Huge:
						</p>
						<p>
							<m>862,070 \div 2 = 431,035</m>, then go to the next whole number and get 431,036.
						</p>
						<p>
							For Small:
						</p>
						<p>
							<m>154,600 \div 2 = 77,300</m>, then go to the next whole number which is 77,301.
						</p>
						<p>
							<m>431,036+77,301 \text{ votes } = 508,337 \text{ votes}</m>
						</p>
						<p>
							Let's also consider the next larger combination of 29 electoral votes: winning Small, Large and Medium, because their populations are smaller than the Huge state.
						</p>
						<p>
							We found above that Small can be won with a bare majority of 77,301 people.
						</p>
						<p>
							For Medium:
						</p>
						<p>
							<m>262,340 \div 2 = 131,170</m>, then go to the next whole number which is 131,171.
						</p>
						<p>
							For Large:
						</p>
						<p>
							<m>581,135 \div 2 = 290,567.5</m>, then go to the next whole number which is 290,568.
						</p>
						<p>
							<m>77,301 + 131,171 + 290,568 \text{ votes } = 499,040 \text{ votes}</m>
						</p>
						<p>
							A candidate can win with 499,040 votes in the combination of the Small, Large and Medium state.
						</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<p>
							The smallest number of votes to win the electoral college is 499,040. What percentage of the population is that? We will divide by the total population to get
						</p>
						<p>
							<m>499,040 \div 1,860,145 = 0.2683.</m>
						</p>
						<p>
							If a candidate had the right combination of states in this made up country, they could win the Electoral College with only 26.8% of the vote.
						</p>
					</li>
